txt.en: Mauhúr's Uruk-hai have been attempting to establish a foothold within the eastern part of the Norcrofts from which to attack Elthengels and other Rohirrim settlements.\n\nReducing the Uruk-infantry will greatly weaken the chances of a direct assault on Elthengels.
'You have done well. Each Uruk you defeat means less danger for the merchants and inhabitants of Elthengels. Their kind would do well to stay clear of the lands of the Eorlingas.'
Mauhúr's Uruk-hai have been attempting to establish a foothold within the eastern part of the Norcrofts from which to attack Elthengels and other Rohirrim settlements.
Many Uruk-hai have attempted to establish an encampment south of Elthengels at Kufuzg.\n\nDefeat the Uruk-hai who reside at Kufuzg and help put an end to the Uruk-leader's threat.
Return to the Guard-captain at the trader's outpost

The Guard-captain of the merchants can be found at the trader's outpost, along the road west of Elthengels.\n\nThe Guard-captain of the trader's outpost is said to reward those able to rid Norcrofts of its Uruk enemies.
